article.description: Kollock helps SC State beat Florida A&M 34-17
article.headline: Kollock helps SC State beat Florida A&M 34-17
article.linkText: Kollock helps SC State beat Florida A&M 34-17
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Andrew Kollock passed for a touchdown and ran for two more as South Carolina State defeated Florida A&M 34-17 on Saturday night, keeping the Rattlers interim coach Corey Fuller winless in two games. South Carolina State held Florida A&M to 46 yards rushing and forced three turnovers. Kollock completed 15 of 23 passes for 224 yards, and the Bulldogs (7-3, 5-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic) remain knotted for the conference lead with Bethune-Cookman and North Carolina A&T. Florida A&M fired Earl Holmes two weeks ago, appointing Fuller to take over. The Rattlers Damien Fleming passed for 284 yards and a pair of touchdowns -- his first for 13 yards to Dennis Hall as FAMU pulled to 13-7. Chase Varnadore added a 35-yard field goal and the Rattlers trailed 13-10 at halftime. But South Carolina State scored twice more in the third quarter, jumping ahead 27-10.
